Wang Wenbin, spokesperson of Chinese Foreign Ministry. Photo: CFP China urges the US to stop its unreasonable crackdown on Chinese firms as trade protectionism will damage the stability of international industrial and supply chains as well as global cooperation on climate change, which will damage the US’ own interests in the end, China’s Foreign Ministry said on Tuesday.Wang Wenbin, spokesperson for the Chinese Foreign Ministry, made the remarks at a press conference on Tuesday, after the US alleged that it will investigate whether Chinese solar module makers illegally circumvented solar tariffs by doing business in four other countries – Cambodia, Malaysia, Thailand and Vietnam.The US Department of Commerce made the decision on Monday, saying that it would act on a petition filed by California-based solar module assembler Auxin Solar, which alleged that Chinese manufacturers shifted production to the four Southeast Asian countries to avoid paying US duties in place for nearly a decade on Chinese-made solar goods, Reuters reported.Wang noted that the country will take all necessary measures to safeguard the legitimate rights and interests of Chinese enterprises.The companies involved are leading Chinese photovoltaic manufacturers including LONGi, Trinasolar and JinkoSolar.LONGi told the Global Times on Tuesday that the company has products that are sold to the US from Vietnam and Malaysia. The company has been following the investigation by the US Department of Commerce, and it will assess the impact and the subsequent outcome of the investigation.